Peru Stocks: Candente, Alturas, Rio Alto, La Cima, Casa Grande

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-14T17:54:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/peru-stocks-candente-alturas-rio-alto-la-cima-casa-grande.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:25 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for the fifth session in six,
losing 1.1 percent to 21,538.51. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index
fell 0.8 percent to 2,960.23.  Miners fell after a decline in U.S. stocks sent the
Standard & Poor’s 500 Index to the lowest level since January,
Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa SAB, said in a
telephone interview.    Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, plunged 9.5 percent to 19 cents.  Candente
Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, dropped
7.9 percent to $1.75.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian
gold exploration company, fell 4.2 percent to $2.29. Gold Fields
La Cima SA (LACIMAI1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields Ltd., slid 1.9
percent to 3.09 soles.    Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, fell 3.2 percent to 15.10 soles after
sugar declined in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  